    <h1 id="hd_id31529004750471" xml-lang="en-US"><variable id="ScriptForge_lib"><link href="text/sbasic/shared/03/lib_ScriptForge.xhp" name="ScriptForge library">The <item type="literal">ScriptForge</item> Library</link></variable></h1>
    <bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id491529070339774">
        <bookmark_value>BASIC ScriptForge library</bookmark_value>
    </bookmark>
    <section id="howtoget">
        <embed href="text/sbasic/shared/00000003.xhp#basiclibhowtoget"/>
    </section>
    <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id51611081179661">The ScriptForge library is a collection of macro scripting resources (services and methods) for LibreOffice that can be invoked from Basic and Python scripts.</paragraph>
    <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id601611082068557">The purpose of this library is to provide a set of services and methods that allow the user to:</paragraph>
    <list type="unordered">
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id101611082103898" role="listitem">Handle arrays, including operations such as sorting, appending, removing, etc.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id721611082131837" role="listitem">Handle dictionaries mapping String keys to objects of any type.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id21611082166730" role="listitem">Handle strings, including replacements, regular expressions, encoding, etc.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id21611082166731" role="listitem">Handle exceptions raised by Basic and ScriptForge.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id21611082166732" role="listitem">Interconnect Basic and Python modules.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id21611082166733" role="listitem">Easily access and manage windows and documents.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id21611082166734" role="listitem">Automate and interact with Calc spreadsheets.</paragraph>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <paragraph id="par_id21611082166735" role="listitem">And much more!</paragraph>
        </listitem>
    </list>

    <note id="par_id901528999850603"><embedvar href="text/sbasic/shared/00000003.xhp#basiclibrarynote" markup="keep"/><br/>
        <item type="literal">GlobalScope.BasicLibraries.LoadLibrary("ScriptForge")</item></note>

    <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id781606153472028">The described modules and classes are invoked from user scripts as "Services". A generic constructor of those services has been designed for that purpose:</paragraph>
    <bascode>
      <paragraph role="bascode" id="bas_id201606153529501">[ScriptForge.][Services.]CreateScriptService("servicename"[, arg0, Arg1, ...])</paragraph>
    </bascode>

    <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id891606153700196">Services from external libraries can be registered with the <literal>RegisterScriptServices(...)</literal> method in order to extend the set of available services.</paragraph>
    <note id="par_id851605659675843"><literal>ScriptForge</literal> Basic library is available from %PRODUCTNAME 7.1 onwards.</note>

    <h1 id="hd_id611611082371135">Further Information</h1>
    <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id301611082387961">The Help pages for all the modules of the <literal>ScriptForge</literal> library are still being prepared.</paragraph>
    <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id651611082443449">If you want to read the Help pages before their final release, you can access <link href="https://help.libreoffice.org/7.2/en-US/text/sbasic/shared/03/lib_ScriptForge.html?DbPAR=BASIC" name="LODev Link">this link</link> that will take you to LibreOfficeDev 7.2 ScriptForge Help page.</paragraph>

    <warning id="par_id611611082695501">Beware that LibreOfficeDev 7.2 is still under development and the contents of Help pages are being actively updated.</warning>
    <section id="SF_InternalUse">
    <warning id="par_id851506659675843">All <literal>ScriptForge</literal> Basic routines or identifiers that are prefixed with an underscore character "_" are reserved for internal use. They are not meant be used in Basic macros.</warning>
    </section>
